The paper discusses a routing protocol for Wireless Sensor Networks (WSN), which falls under the category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The paper also addresses security concerns in WSN, which could place it under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The use of clustering techniques and signal-to-noise ratio (SNR) based selection of Cluster Heads (CH) involves data processing and optimization, which could place the paper under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of error recovery and packet reception rate (PRR), which could place it under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT).
